HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 106
BY REPRESENTATIVE FREEMAN
COMMENDATIONS: Commends the Most Reverend James F. Checchio on becoming the
Fifteenth Archbishop of New Orleans
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend the Most Reverend James F. Checchio on becoming the Fifteenth Archbishop
3 of New Orleans.
4 WHEREAS, Archbishop Checchio was born on April 21, 1966, in Camden, New
5 Jersey, and is one of four children born to James and Helen Checchio; he was raised in
6 Collingswood, where he attended St. John School, and he attended Pope Paul VI High
7 School in Haddon Township; and
8 WHEREAS, Archbishop Checchio earned a bachelor of arts degree in philosophy
9 from the University of Scranton and studied at North American College in Rome; he holds
10 a master of business administration degree from LaSalle University and a doctorate of canon
11 law and bachelor of sacred theology degree from the University of Saint Thomas Aquinas
12 in Rome; and
13 WHEREAS, Archbishop Checchio was ordained a priest for the Diocese of Camden
14 at the Cathedral of the Immaculate Conception on June 20, 1992; he held various roles
15 within the diocese, including secretary to Bishop James T. McHugh, vice chancellor, director
16 of communications, moderator of the curia, and episcopal vicar for administration of the
17 diocese; he also served in the tribunal and as a member of the College of Consultors,
18 Presbyteral Council, Investment Committee, and Diocesan Finance Council; and
19 WHEREAS, Archbishop Checchio served as parochial vicar at St. Agnes Parish and
20 assisted at St. Jude Parish, both in Blackwood County, New Jersey; he also served as a
