1 summer parochial vicar at St. Peter Parish in Merchantville and St. Peter Celestine Parish
2 in Cherry Hill; and
3 WHEREAS, Archbishop Checchio was appointed a Chaplain to His Holiness by
4 Pope John Paul II and granted the title of monsignor in 2000; he served as rector of the
5 Pontifical North American College in Rome from January 2006 to January 2016, during
6 which the college enjoyed its highest enrollment of American seminarians since the 1960s;
7 and
8 WHEREAS, Archbishop Checchio was appointed a Prelate of Honor, a papal honor
9 bestowed upon diocesan priests, by Pope Benedict XVI in 2011; and
10 WHEREAS, Archbishop Checchio was named the Bishop of the Diocese of
11 Metuchen by Pope Francis on March 8, 2016, and was ordained and installed as the Fifth
12 Bishop of Metuchen on May 3, 2016; and
13 WHEREAS, Archbishop Checchio was appointed Coadjutor Archbishop of New
14 Orleans by Pope Leo XIV on September 24, 2025, and began his ministry with a mass of
15 welcome at St. Louis Cathedral on November 18, 2025; and
16 WHEREAS, Archbishop Checchio formally became the Fifteenth Archbishop of
17 New Orleans on February 11, 2026, after Pope Leo XIV accepted the resignation of Most
18 Reverend Gregory M. Aymond; and
19 WHEREAS, outside of his role with the Archdiocese of New Orleans, Archbishop
20 Checchio serves the United States Conference of Catholic Bishops as conference treasurer,
21 chairman of the Committee on Budget and Finance, vice chairman of the Committee on
22 Priorities and Plans, and member of the Executive Committee and Member Committee; and
23 WHEREAS, Archbishop Checchio is a member of the Papal Foundation board of
24 trustees, an appointed member of the board of trustees for the Basilica of the National Shrine
25 of the Immaculate Conception, a member of the Seton Hall University board of regents; a
26 member of the Seton Hall University board of overseers for Immaculate Conception
27 Seminary, a member of the board of directors for the National Catholic Bioethics Center, and
28 a member of the board of visitors for the Catholic University of America Busch School of
29 Business; and
